you can make mistakes and you should not assume you 100% know the answer to some error or question 
you encounter. Instead, try to test your knowledge by taking simple steps. For example, when you are
presented with some keyError, something you could do is check what keys are available in the 
relevant object instead of assuming you know what is available in there. 
